						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab set up in the field called Guttappanavara Hola</hi></p>						

						<p>Vīra-Nārāyaṇa (Bhillama)—A.D. 1187.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the king's regnal <hi rend="bold">year 2, Plavaṅga, Kārtika, Pūrṇimā, Monday,</hi> regularly corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1187, October 19, Monday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of land for a feeding house <hi rend="italic">(satra)</hi> by Rēchibhaṭṭof <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kalakere</hi> after purchasing it from Daṇḍanāyaka <hi rend="bold">Vikramāditya,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">prabhu</hi> of Kalakeṟe. <hi rend="italic">See</hi> No. 174 below and Introduction.</p>						

						</summary>
